---
import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';
import { resolve } from 'node:path';
import HeroDiagram from './HeroDiagram.astro';

let version = '';
try {
  const conf = JSON.parse(readFileSync(resolve('../../apps/desktop/src-tauri/tauri.conf.json'), 'utf8'));
  version = conf.version ? `v${conf.version}` : '';
} catch {}
---

<section
  id="hero"
  class="relative min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-center text-center px-4 sm:px-6 overflow-hidden"
>
  <div
    class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none"
    style="background: radial-gradient(ellipse 80% 60% at 50% 40%, rgba(103,232,249,0.05) 0%, transparent 70%);"
    aria-hidden="true"
  ></div>

  <div
    class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none opacity-[0.03]"
    style="background-image: linear-gradient(#67e8f9 1px, transparent 1px), linear-gradient(90deg, #67e8f9 1px, transparent 1px); background-size: 40px 40px;"
    aria-hidden="true"
  ></div>

  <div class="relative z-10 w-full flex flex-col items-center">

    <!-- Badge + H1 -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center w-full">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full border border-[#2a2a3d] bg-[#1c1c27] text-[#67e8f9] text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase mb-8">
        <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[#67e8f9] animate-pulse"></span>
        Now available on macOS
      </div>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-black text-white leading-normal tracking-tight mb-6">
        <span class="block">Your local encrypted memory,</span>
        <span
          class="block bg-clip-text text-transparent"
          style="background-image: linear-gradient(135deg, #67e8f9 0%, #a78bfa 100%);"
        >indexed with $0 for deterministic recall</span>
      </h1>
    </div>

    <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-[#c4c6d6] tracking-wide text-center mb-8 -mt-2 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      Auditable, indexed and deterministically managed with zero LLM calls, the free download of Graphnosis precisely stores and recalls memories for every <span class="text-[#f0f0f5]">AI client</span> — and for private, local tools and projects of your own:
      <span class="text-[#f0f0f5]">home automation · personal agents · robotics · research · writing</span>.
      One consistent, consolidated memory for all of them.
    </p>

    <!-- Rotating flow diagram -->
    <div class="w-full max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 mb-10">
      <HeroDiagram variant="consumer" />
    </div>

    <!-- Cross-client stories -->
    <div class="w-full max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-left mb-12 mt-0">

        <article class="bg-[#1c1c27] border border-[#2a2a3d] rounded-xl p-6 flex flex-col gap-4">
          <div class="text-center flex flex-col items-center gap-1.5">
            <span class="inline-block text-base font-black tracking-[0.22em] uppercase px-4 py-1.5 rounded-md bg-[#67e8f9]/10 text-[#67e8f9] border border-[#67e8f9]/30">● Online</span>
            <span class="text-xs font-mono text-[#52525b] uppercase tracking-wider">SaaS sources</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-[#c4c6d6] font-mono flex-wrap">
            <span>flow</span>
            <span class="text-[#36C5F0] font-semibold">Slack</span>
            <span>+</span>
            <span class="text-[#F78424] font-semibold">GitHub</span>
            <span>→</span>
            <span class="text-[#6366F1] font-semibold">Cursor</span>
            <span>+</span>
            <span class="text-[#238636] font-semibold">Copilot</span>
            <span>+</span>
            <span class="text-[#D97757] font-semibold">Claude Code</span>
            <span>+</span>
            <span class="text-[#D97757] font-semibold">Claude Cowork</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[#f0f0f5] text-xl font-semibold leading-snug">"Cross-memory of a recurring code bug. Fix it. Note down the lessons learned."</p>
          <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-base leading-relaxed">You <u>auto-ingest</u> your <span class="font-semibold" style="color:#36C5F0">Slack</span> export and <span class="font-semibold" style="color:#F78424">GitHub</span> PR history into Graphnosis. In <span class="font-semibold" style="color:#6366F1">Cursor</span> and <span class="font-semibold" style="color:#238636">Copilot Chat</span>, you ask <span class="bg-amber-400/20 text-amber-100 font-mono text-base px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">recall the report about yesterday's recurring crash</span> — it surfaces the <span class="font-semibold" style="color:#36C5F0">Slack</span> thread where the root cause was debated, plus the <span class="font-semibold" style="color:#F78424">GitHub</span> PR that "fixed" it and the later commit that silently undid it. You switch to <span class="font-semibold" style="color:#D97757">Claude Code</span> and implement the real fix with full context already loaded. Then you tell <span class="font-semibold" style="color:#D97757">Claude Cowork</span>: <span class="bg-amber-400/20 text-amber-100 font-mono text-base px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">remember the lessons learned from the latest recurring crash</span> — it already knows what you're talking about.</p>
          <div class="flex gap-2 mt-auto flex-wrap">
            <span class="text-sm font-mono px-3 py-1 rounded bg-[#13131a] text-[#67e8f9] border border-[#2a2a3d]">ingest</span>
            <span class="text-sm font-mono px-3 py-1 rounded bg-[#13131a] text-[#67e8f9] border border-[#2a2a3d]">recall</span>
            <span class="text-sm font-mono px-3 py-1 rounded bg-[#13131a] text-[#67e8f9] border border-[#2a2a3d]">remember</span>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="bg-[#1c1c27] border border-[#2a2a3d] rounded-xl p-6 flex flex-col gap-4">
          <div class="text-center flex flex-col items-center gap-1.5">
            <span class="inline-block text-base font-black tracking-[0.22em] uppercase px-4 py-1.5 rounded-md bg-[#a78bfa]/10 text-[#a78bfa] border border-[#a78bfa]/30">○ Offline</span>
            <span class="text-xs font-mono text-[#52525b] uppercase tracking-wider">LAN · sensors · local LLM</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-[#c4c6d6] font-mono flex-wrap">
            <span>flow</span>
            <span class="text-[#a78bfa] font-semibold">Home Assistant</span>
            <span>+</span>
            <span class="text-[#a78bfa] font-semibold">MQTT logs</span>
            <span>+</span>
            <span class="text-[#a78bfa] font-semibold">NAS notes</span>
            <span>→</span>
            <span class="text-[#a78bfa] font-semibold">Local LLM (Ollama)</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[#f0f0f5] text-xl font-semibold leading-snug">"Why does the upstairs heater kick on at 3 AM every week? Stop it."</p>
          <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-base leading-relaxed">Your home runs on <span class="font-semibold" style="color:#a78bfa">Home Assistant</span> on a Raspberry Pi, with motion sensors, temperature probes, and a smart thermostat all talking <span class="font-semibold" style="color:#a78bfa">MQTT</span> over your LAN. You <u>auto-ingest</u> the broker's event logs, your Home Assistant automation YAMLs, and your handwritten notes about quirks of the boiler — all from your <span class="font-semibold" style="color:#a78bfa">NAS</span>, never the cloud. Graphnosis indexes everything as a private engram. You ask the bundled <span class="font-semibold" style="color:#a78bfa">local LLM</span>: <span class="bg-amber-400/20 text-amber-100 font-mono text-base px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">recall what triggers the heater between 2 and 4 AM</span> — it correlates the motion-sensor false-positives in the hallway with the "heat-on-presence" rule you wrote six months ago and forgot about. You tell it: <span class="bg-amber-400/20 text-amber-100 font-mono text-base px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">edit the automation — ignore hallway motion between midnight and 6 AM</span>. Diff approved, YAML patched, broker reloaded. No data ever leaves your house.</p>
          <div class="flex gap-2 mt-auto flex-wrap">
            <span class="text-sm font-mono px-3 py-1 rounded bg-[#13131a] text-[#a78bfa] border border-[#2a2a3d]">ingest</span>
            <span class="text-sm font-mono px-3 py-1 rounded bg-[#13131a] text-[#a78bfa] border border-[#2a2a3d]">recall</span>
            <span class="text-sm font-mono px-3 py-1 rounded bg-[#13131a] text-[#a78bfa] border border-[#2a2a3d]">edit</span>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="bg-[#1c1c27] border border-[#2a2a3d] rounded-xl p-6 flex flex-col gap-4">
          <div class="text-center flex flex-col items-center gap-1.5">
            <span class="inline-block text-base font-black tracking-[0.22em] uppercase px-4 py-1.5 rounded-md bg-gradient-to-r from-[#67e8f9]/15 to-[#a78bfa]/15 text-[#f0f0f5] border border-[#67e8f9]/30">◐ Online + Offline</span>
            <span class="text-xs font-mono text-[#52525b] uppercase tracking-wider">Nonprofit · hybrid</span>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-[#c4c6d6] font-mono flex-wrap">
            <span>flow</span>
            <span class="text-[#36C5F0] font-semibold">Slack</span>
            <span>+</span>
            <span class="text-[#a78bfa] font-semibold">scanned files</span>
            <span>+</span>
            <span class="text-[#a78bfa] font-semibold">local docs</span>
            <span>→</span>
            <span class="text-[#D97757] font-semibold">Claude Code</span>
            <span>+</span>
            <span class="text-[#D97757] font-semibold">Claude Desktop</span>
            <span>+</span>
            <span class="text-[#0EA5E9] font-semibold">Zed</span>
            <span>+</span>
            <span class="text-[#D97757] font-semibold">Claude Cowork</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-[#f0f0f5] text-xl font-semibold leading-snug">"Our key volunteer left. Who holds the knowledge — and what's at risk?"</p>
          <p class="text-[#c4c6d6] text-base leading-relaxed">Your literacy nonprofit lives partly in <span class="font-semibold" style="color:#36C5F0">Slack</span> volunteer channels and partly in <span class="font-semibold" style="color:#a78bfa">scanned paper files</span> on a shared drive — intake forms, grant reports, handwritten meeting minutes Maria kept for years. You <u>auto-ingest</u> both the Slack export <em>and</em> the scanned PDFs (OCR'd locally) into Graphnosis. Maria resigns on short notice. In <span class="font-semibold" style="color:#D97757">Claude Code</span>: <span class="bg-amber-400/20 text-amber-100 font-mono text-base px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">edit the org chart — Maria is no longer the lead for the youth literacy program</span> — every reference updates. Before the board call, <span class="font-semibold" style="color:#D97757">Claude Desktop</span>: <span class="bg-amber-400/20 text-amber-100 font-mono text-base px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">recall everything Maria owned and flag what's at risk</span> — three programs and an unfinished grant surface instantly, alongside two signed donor commitments buried in the scanned files. You pick up the grant draft in <span class="font-semibold" style="color:#0EA5E9">Zed</span>, then close in <span class="font-semibold" style="color:#D97757">Claude Cowork</span>: <span class="bg-amber-400/20 text-amber-100 font-mono text-base px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">draft an onboarding brief for Maria's replacement</span> — shipped before her last day.</p>
          <div class="flex gap-2 mt-auto flex-wrap">
            <span class="text-sm font-mono px-3 py-1 rounded bg-[#13131a] text-[#67e8f9] border border-[#2a2a3d]">ingest</span>
            <span class="text-sm font-mono px-3 py-1 rounded bg-[#13131a] text-[#67e8f9] border border-[#2a2a3d]">edit</span>
            <span class="text-sm font-mono px-3 py-1 rounded bg-[#13131a] text-[#67e8f9] border border-[#2a2a3d]">recall</span>
          </div>
        </article>

      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Description + CTAs -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center w-full">
      <p
        id="graphnosis"
        class="text-5xl sm:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-black tracking-tight mt-10 mb-2 bg-clip-text text-transparent scroll-mt-24"
        style="background-image: linear-gradient(135deg, #67e8f9 0%, #a78bfa 100%);"
      >Graphnosis</p>
      <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-[#c4c6d6] tracking-wide mb-6">Your local encrypted memory, indexed for deterministic recall — auditable</p>
      <img src="/graphnosis-logo.png" alt="Graphnosis" class="w-72 h-72 mx-auto mb-6" />
      <div class="border-t border-[#2a2a3d] pt-12 text-center">
        <p class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-[#f0f0f5] max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-snug">
          Your files are the neocortex. Your AI is the prefrontal cortex. What's always been missing is the <span class="text-[#67e8f9]">AI hippocampus</span> — the part that indexes, connects, and makes knowledge retrievable.
          <br /><br />
          <span class="bg-clip-text text-transparent" style="background-image: linear-gradient(135deg, #67e8f9 0%, #a78bfa 100%);">
            Graphnosis is your AI hippocampus — local, encrypted, private, and deterministic.
          </span>
          <br /><br />
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-t border-[#2a2a3d] pt-12 text-center">
        <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-[#c4c6d6] max-w-xl mx-auto leading-relaxed mb-10">
          Graphnosis' indexing pipeline is deterministic and runs entirely on your device. No AI API is called.
          <br />
          <span class="text-[#f0f0f5]">The cost to build your local, encrypted second cortex: $0.</span>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4 mb-4">
        <a
          href="/download/mac"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-8 py-4 rounded-full bg-[#67e8f9] hover:bg-[#4dd6e8] text-[#13131a] font-bold text-lg transition-colors shadow-lg shadow-[#67e8f9]/20"
        >
          Download{version ? ` ${version}` : ''} for macOS
        </a>
        <a
          href="/getting-started/overview"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 px-8 py-4 rounded-full border border-[#2a2a3d] hover:border-[#67e8f9] text-[#f0f0f5] font-semibold text-lg transition-colors"
        >
          Read the docs
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" />
          </svg>
        </a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-[#c4c6d6] mb-8 mt-3 tracking-wide">
        Your local encrypted memory, indexed for deterministic recall — auditable
      </p>

      <p class="text-sm text-[#c4c6d6]">
        <span class="text-[#f0f0f5] font-semibold">Local-first</span>
        &nbsp;·&nbsp;
        <span class="text-[#f0f0f5] font-semibold">No cloud AI during ingest</span>
        &nbsp;·&nbsp;
        <span class="text-[#f0f0f5] font-semibold">Open-source engine</span>
        &nbsp;·&nbsp; Works with Claude, Cursor, Copilot, Zed, and more
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>

  <div
    class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 h-px"
    style="background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent 0%, #2a2a3d 30%, #67e8f9 50%, #2a2a3d 70%, transparent 100%);"
    aria-hidden="true"
  ></div>
</section>
